parameters:
Zerachiel: There's no doubt that Effy's
curse is the work of the stargazing
goddess Eden.

Zerachiel: While playing the role of the
Orpheus Cult's leader, I was cursing
Effy.

Aries: It is to extract the Seventh
Curse from Lady Effy, isn't it?

Zerachiel: One of the forbidden arts
that feeds on souls, spreads toxins, and
annihilates all life...

Zerachiel: With even the Seventh Curse,
I can obtain the world.

Lala: First of all, I have a question.
Why does the stargazing goddess want to
obtain the world?

Aries: ...It's a grudge from a thousand
years ago.

\CLIn the primordial era, there were many
gods in this world.

\CLAfter spending a long time, the gods
came to a conclusion.

\CLThe world is too vast to live with just
the gods.

\CLWhat if we create a new race and live
together? Wouldn't that be fun?

\CLAnd so, the two chosen by the Creator
were the two gods.

\CLThe life created by the Stargazing
Goddess Eden was a high-level
organism...

\CLThey are beings such as angels, dragon
people, giants, and divine beasts.

\CLThey possess overwhelming lifespan and
power, on the other hand, their
reproductive ability is very low.

\CLThey are called the \c[6]people of
Eden\c[0], due to their lineage with
Eden.

\CLThe life created by the \c[6]Goddess of
Fortune, Michelin\c[0] was many races...

\CLHumans, beastmen, mermaids, elves, and
dwarves are famous.

\CLCompared to the people of Eden, they are
beings who are inferior in terms of
power, magical power, and even lifespan.
They are called the \c[6]people of
Michelin\c[0].

\CLThe two races have spent a long time
together, cooperating with each other
without any conflict.
\CLUntil that day, a thousand years ago...

\CLA thousand years ago... a massive
meteorite fell onto this planet.

\CLThe planet was supposed to disappear
without a trace due to a massive
meteorite that even the gods, combining
their powers, couldn't avoid.

\CLBut, a hero appeared who twisted that
fate.

\CLThe Emperor, the founding ancestor of
the \c[6]people of Michelin\c[0], who
built the later empire.

\CLHe used forbidden magic to protect this
planet.

\CLA large-scale ritual is activated using
the continent where the \c[6]people of
Eden\c[0], who possess high magical
power, live as a catalyst...

\CLThe meteorite came from a different
world than this planet...

\CLThe \c[1]people of Michelin\c[0]
succeeded in surviving by being isolated
in the \c[1]other side world\c[0].

\CLI lost my hometown, lost my comrades,
and was betrayed by the \c[6]people of
Michelin\c[0]...

\CLThe people of Eden are considering
revenge.
\CLThat's why they are preparing like this.
Lala: You guys sure know a lot...

Zerachiel: ...You didn't learn it since
you were a child? I'm surprised that
Lala doesn't know about it.

Lala: Ah, I'm not interested in history
at all!!

Zerachiel: I never expected Aries to be
the daughter of the Demon Lord.

Lala: You don't look like a demon at
all, do you?

Aries: My mother is a beast person, and
that blood runs thick in me.

Zerachiel: I was helped by an incredible
person, you know.
Zerachiel: Well then, shall we go soon?

Lala: We're heading to the Castle of
Vaal, right?

Zerachiel: Yeah, that's where we'll have
our final meeting.

Aries: A joint military invasion by the
Demon Lord's army and the members of the
cult...

Aries: We will attack the Transference
Gate \c[6]Absorb Gate\c[0] and
infiltrate the other side of the
world...

Aries: I will rescue Lady Effy from the
Seventh Curse.

Lala: Angels may have high physical
abilities, but their numbers are few.

Zerachiel: They will surely bring in a
large number of homunculi, won't they?

Zerachiel: In other words, this is our
chance to board when our forces are not
yet fully prepared.

Aries: Zerachiel-sama, please take this
with you.

Received the \c[6]Ring of the Holy
Maiden\c[0]!

Aries: This is something I received from
Lady Effy.

Aries: I want you to give it to
Zerachiel-sama.
Zerachiel: I will gratefully accept it.
Aries: And this is from me.

Aries: I have infused my magical power
into it. It will surely be of use to
you.

Zerachiel: Aries, I've been indebted to
you for everything.

Zerachiel: Thank you. I'll express my
gratitude in advance.

Aries: It's still too early to say thank
you.

Lala: Hehe, yes. Let's celebrate when
everything is over.
Lala: You really became a dog, huh?

Marnagarm: The Demon Lord and the other
comrades are already waiting at Vaal's
castle.

Aries: Marnagarm, I heard that you
transferred my father to Logres...

Marnagarm: ...No need for thanks. I
can't just hand over the Seventh Curse
to the Star God.
Lala: You're really not obedient at all.

Marnagarm: When you're ready, speak to
me. We'll teleport to Vaal's castle.

Zerachiel: (Let's make sure we're fully
prepared and head to the castle)

Zerachiel: We need to find Aries. I
think she might be indoors.
